"n.手枪皮套 【英】 n. 手枪皮套(a pistol case) 【考】 dagger : scabbard / pistol : holster(匕首装在剑鞘里/手 枪装在手枪皮套里) n. (系在腰上的)手枪皮套 【记】源于hol = hold(v 拿住n 船舱)－拿住手枪的东西－皮套 【类】dagger: scabbard = pistol: holster匕首装在剑鞘里 = 手枪装在手枪皮套里 【记】hole + 音：手套→有个洞象皮手套般的皮套；hold 装东西的 + er 东西 holster (n.)  ""leather case for a pistol,"" 1660s, probably from Old English heolster, earlier helustr ""concealment, hiding place,"" from Proto-Germanic *hulfti- (cognates: Old High German hulft ""cover, case, sheath,"" Old Norse hulstr ""case, sheath,"" Middle Dutch holster, German Holfster ""holster""), from PIE *kel- (2) ""to cover, to hide"" (see cell). Intermediate forms are wanting, and the modern word could as well be from the Norse or Dutch cognates. holster (v.)  by 1902, from holster (n.). Related: Holstered; holstering."
